Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: MindMaple Inc. is the creator of MindMaple software. MindMaple is a software product that allows the user to create mind maps, which are tools used by professionals worldwide for problem solving, developing business strategies and planning, education, and many other purposes. Some mind mapping programs restrict the user's mind maps to compact, pre-determined formats and structures, which can be helpful to beginning users but is often counterproductive for advanced users who have developed personal styles of mind mapping. Other programs allow the user complete creative freedom when making mind maps, letting the user organize and place ideas however they choose, which can be overwhelming for new users. MindMaple's software integrates these two needs of the user, by including structured mind mapping formats but also offering endless possibilities for creativity by allowing the user to change and personalize their mind maps freely. Using MindMaple, beginning users can work at their own pace to discover a unique style of mind mapping and improve their productivity. MindMaple is a product ideal for both beginning and experienced mind map users, and includes features allowing the integration of attachments, pictures, comments, and more into the user's maps and allowing export to Microsoft Word, Excel, and Powerpoint.

Description: The San Gabriel Basin Water Quality Authority is a government agency in charge of groundwater quality control in the San Gabriel Basin.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The San Gabriel Basin Water Quality Authority (WQA) was established by the State Legislature (SB1679) on February 11, 1993, to develop, finance, and implement groundwater treatment programs in the San Gabriel Basin.  The San Gabriel Basin is the primary source of drinking water for more than 1 million people in Alhambra, Irwindale, La Puente, Rosemead, Azusa, Baldwin Park, City of Industry, El Monte, South El Monte, West Covina, and other areas of the San Gabriel Valley.  In 1979, industrial solvents and other contaminants were identified in groundwater in the San Gabriel Valley. The contamination at the site is believed to be the result of decades of improper chemical handling and disposal practices. As a result, water suppliers had to shut down wells and large portions of the basin were placed on the federal Superfund cleanup list in 1984. The WQA was created to manage and coordinate the cleanup with local, state, and federal agencies.
Industry Groups: Government and Military, Natural Resources, Other, Professional Services, Social Impact, Sustainability

Full Description: As one of the country’s elite independent life insurance and estate planning firms, Parq Advisors serves ultra-affluent individuals and families, including some of the world’s most famous athletes, entertainers, executives, entrepreneurs and business owners. We are often brought into the nation’s leading law firms, accounting firms, business management firms and sports franchises to ensure their clients and players receive the best care relating to their wealth protection and wealth transfer planning. Our philosophy revolves around integrity, transparency, professionalism, relationships and mastery. At Parq Advisors, we have: More than 115 years combined  firm experience. A team-based approach, providing each client with individual consideration. Working relationships with estate planning attorneys, accountants, business managers, bankers and investment advisors to help ensure that the insurance planning fits seamlessly into the overall financial plan. Relationships with over 50 carriers, providing our clients with the ability to obtain optimal pricing with the most stable and reputable carriers in the industry. Since 1978, M Financial's network of independent insurance, investment, and executive benefit firms has served the needs of ultra-affluent individuals, corporate executives, successful entrepreneurs, and Fortune 1000 companies. At its inception, Parq Advisors was established using a team-based approach to planning. Traditionally, the industry standard for providing service is limited to a single advisor approach. Fundamentally, Parq Advisors believes that this approach limits clients’ exposure to new ideas and puts them at a disadvantage during the discovery and implementation process. Consequently, at Parq Advisors, clients receive the personal attention of both their direct advisor in addition to at least two other team members, including a dedicated case manager. Each Parq Advisors team member has been hand-selected and operates under our clearly defined mission, vision and values. The Parq Advisors legacy is reflected through our clients; our service to them is what defines our success and keeps us at the top of our industry.
